#include &quot;vmlinux.h&quot; vmlinux.h is generated code. it contains all of the type definitions that your running Linux kernel uses in it&rsquo;s own source code. This is an important concept to wrap your head around so let me explain.
When you build Linux one of the output artifacts is a file called vmlinux.
